# Week 03 – HTML Structure and CSS Styling

## 🎯 Objective
Apply **HTML structure** and **CSS styling** using all three methods:
- Inline CSS
- Internal (document-level) CSS
- External CSS

Demonstrate multiple selector types:
- Element, Class, ID, Group, Descendant, and Pseudo-class.

---

## 📂 What Was Done
- Created a **single webpage** (`index.html`) with the following sections:
  - **Header:** Name + Title
  - **Navigation Menu:** Anchor links to each section
  - **About Section:** Paragraph + Image
  - **Skills Section:** Unordered list of skills
  - **Daily Routine Section:** Ordered list of daily activities

- Applied **CSS styling** using:
  - **External CSS (`style.css`):** Background color, typography
  - **Internal CSS (`<style>` block):** Navigation menu styling, section headings
  - **Inline CSS:** Applied to fewer than 5 elements (e.g., header text alignment, italic paragraph)

---

### HTML Structure
- Header with `id="header"`
- Navigation menu using `<nav><ul><li><a>>`
- About section with text and image
- Skills section with list items
- Daily routine section with ordered list

### CSS Demonstrations
- **Element selector:** `p { color: #333; }`
- **Class selector:** `.section { padding: 20px; }`
- **ID selector:** `#header { text-align: center; }`
- **Group selector:** `h1, h2, h3 { font-family: Verdana; }`
- **Descendant selector:** `nav ul li a { font-weight: bold; }`
- **Pseudo-class:** `nav ul li a:hover { background-color: #555; }`

---

## ⚡ Challenges Faced
- Ensuring proper separation of styles between external, internal, and inline CSS.
- Managing selector specificity when multiple styles applied to the same element.
- Linking the external stylesheet correctly so styles loaded in the browser.

